A Malaysian woman who was allegedly enslaved for 30 years in south London after joining a Left-wing sect has been reunited with her older sister.

Aishah Wahab, 69, who disappeared in the early Seventies after becoming a member of a communist collective, walked free from a flat in Brixton earlier this month.

She finally met with retired teacher Kamar Mahtum, 73, last night after she flew into Heathrow two days ago.

