Miss Wahab won a Commonwealth 
scholarship to study surveying in the UK and moved here in 1968 with her
fiance Omar Munir.

But she soon became involved in extremist politics 
and turned her back on her middle-class upbringing.

She is believed to have fallen under the spell of Aravindan Balakrishnan and his partner 
Chanda, who were last week arrested on suspicion of holding three women 
against their will for more than three decades in south London.

